Usefull Linus commands:-
********************************************apache server********************************
	Restart apache server
		sudo /etc/init.d/apache2 restart
		
	Edit php.ini file

	/etc/php5/apache2$ gedit php.ini
********************************************sqlite***************************************
Accessing sqlite from terminal in linux:-

$ sqlite3
(.tables or .databases)
Accessing Sqlite rom termminal in a rail application

$rails dbconsole

Create file in ubuntu 

$touch abc.txt
$gedit abc.txt
$locate abc.txt


*****************************************mongo-db***************************************
$sudo apt-get install mongodb-clients
$sudo apt-get install mongodb-server
sudo apt-get install mongodb
To enable rest support in a mongodb 
	sudo gedit /etc/mongodb.conf
	adding this line:- rest = true
	sudo restart mongodb

start the mongo db server
$mongod 
start the mongo db with rest service

Accessing mongo db from the terminal
mongo

Mongodb log file path:-
	/var/log/mongodb/mongodb.log

Mongodb lock file path:-
sudo gedit /var/lib/mongodb/mongod.lock

$sudo start mongodb ,$mongod --rest
$sudo stop mongodb

mongodb in browser
http://localhost:28017/
http://www.mongodb.org/display/DOCS/SQL+to+Mongo+Mapping+Chart
http://www.mongodb.org/display/DOCS/Ruby+Language+Center
http://www.mongodb.org/display/DOCS/Http+Interface
******************************************ruby language concept******************************
Unicorn:-
	Unicorn is a cool new Ruby HTTP server, and we like it because itâ€™s Unix.
    Unicorn is an HTTP server for Rack applications designed to only serve fast clients on low-latency, 
    high-bandwidth connections and take advantage of features in Unix/Unix-like kernels.

Nginx:- 
	nginx [engine x] is an HTTP and reverse proxy server, as well as a mail proxy server, 
	written by Igor Sysoev. For a long time, it has been running on many heavily loaded Russian sites including Yandex, 
	Mail.Ru, VKontakte, and Rambler. According to Netcraft nginx served or proxied 10.09% busiest sites in April 2012. 
	Here are some of the success stories: FastMail.FM, Wordpress.com.
 


